<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-07-05T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-07-05T01:00:00-05:00" n="753" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d753">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M)/47<hi rend="superscript">13/22</hi>: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">La Bourboule</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-05T08:00:00+02:00">July
                                        5, 1940—8 a.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received July 7—9:33 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>18. My number 12 of July 3, noon.<note n="28" xml:id="d753fn28">Not
                                    printed.</note> The Ministry of Colonies has been
                                    discovered<note n="29" xml:id="d753fn29">The Ministry of
                                    Colonies was in the process of moving from Bordeaux to
                                    Vichy.</note> and Chauvel<note n="30" xml:id="d753fn30">Jean
                                    Chauvel, Chief of the Far Eastern Division of the French Foreign
                                    Office.</note> stated yesterday that a telegram ordering the
                                immediate release of our wolfram ore and antimony in Indochina had
                                gone forward.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>